Yoshi Sudarso is an actor based in Los Angeles, known for his roles on Power Rangers Dino Charge, Bullet Train, Buffalo Boys, etc. He’s a digital content creator that focuses on fitness, fashion, geek/anime culture and as of recent, lifestyle and family content. He’s created a worldwide audience through multiple mediums of content, but with a greater focus in America and his home country of Indonesia.

20+ years ago I moved to America and met the most amazing girl

10+ years ago we started dating and, both being cheerleaders, we decided to take “Nane Totem” photos, the last slide is the very first one we took (I think….)

8 years ago we got married and continued to travel and take these photos

3 years ago we decided to start a family beyond just the two of us

Last month we went on a family vacation w our two boys and realized we hadn’t taken “Nane Totem” photos in a long time

Someday I won’t be able to do this anymore, w them getting bigger and me getting older. So I train, I want that time to come later than sooner. 

Sarah, Sylas, Zekariah, you are my everything. Daddy kangen banget sama kalian ❤️❤️
Pool day was much needed 🥰
Goodbye Herbert, til next we meet! 👨🏻
This was so much fun, a much needed break in between heavy sets and training to failure. I’ve found such a wonderful community w these people here in Jakarta. Thanks for welcoming me in ❤️❤️

We’re 6 weeks out now. I have never pushed my body to this point out of fear and w the excuses of not having enough time, the right tools, knowledge, etc. But truthfully it’s because of my fear of failure, that’s why I know I have to do this. I have all of those things right in front of me now, all that’s left is for me to actually do this. So we’re doing it. Im excited, and tbh the worst thing that can happen is I lose, but I’m the process achieve a body like I’ve never thought possible. It honestly doesn’t feel real to be starting this journey. Thank you for your guidance, Sifu Heintje and Abra! 

Not having access to my usual kitchen has been tough on my diet, because eating out everyday and every meal is NOT ideal, which is why I’m so glad to be working w MoonMate to get my nutrition on track. Their ready made foods that are yummy, packed w protein, are so easy to prep, all I need is a microwave and maybe make some rice to go along with it. Sometimes I just eat it right out of the package if I’m lazy to plate it 😅

Bali, I’ll see you in November!

Final week going into ICN. Got sick and had to take a few days off into our final week of prep here. It sucks, I wish it wasn’t the case, but that changes nothing. We’re still gonna go to Bali, stand up on that stage, and give it everything we got. Today we get back into the gym and we hit it hard and have zero regrets. As my coach would say, “by Saturday, day before you even step onto that stage, you’re a winner, you did this, so be proud of that.”
But wouldn’t it be nice to walk home w a medal? So I’m coming for that medal!

It wasn’t the result I hoped for, but I fully understand why. The other contestants were amazing and brought their A game. 

I now see that I have so much to work on. I’m not done, I’m coming back w a vengeance. I pushed hard, but that wasn’t enough. So now we go back into the lab and reassess. Hit rock bottom, so there’s nowhere to go but up! 

But today, my coach said that he was proud of me, and THAT, made it all worth it. All the water I didn’t drink, the food I restricted, the weights I lifted. Next we go even beyond that. Thank you for everything, Sifu!!
